Weekend Assignment : Date 24/3/17

Q1. Automate the following scenario : 
            1. Open the new tab in same window and load a web page in newly open window. 
            2. Access an element in the new tab.
            3. Get the control back to the previous open tab and acces any element in that window. 
Q2. Automate Drop down or select an option in drop down feature using Action Class not using Select Class.
Q3. Automate the following scenario: 
            1. Open an web page. Load an another page in same tab. Go back to previous page using driver.navigate().back()
            2. Practice to use driver.navigate().forward()
            3. Practice to use driver.navigate().refresh()
            4. Practice to use driver.navigate().to(URL)
            
Q4. Automate to handle the Alert that appears to take input of yes, No, Cancel, ok from the user. Automate the alerts appearing on link http://the-internet.herokuapp.com/javascript_alerts. Use the following methods of class Alert to automate: 

       accept() To accept the alert 
       dismiss() To dismiss the alert 
       getText() To get the text of the alert 
       sendKeys() To write some text to the alert 
       
       Sample Code: 
       d1.navigate().to("http://the-internet.herokuapp.com/javascript_alerts");
	    	WebElement button=d1.findElement(By.xpath(".//*[@id='content']/div/ul/li[1]/button"));
	   	 button.click();
		   Alert simpleAlert = d1.switchTo().alert();
		  	String alertText = simpleAlert.getText();
			 System.out.println("Alert text is " + alertText);
			 simpleAlert.accept();
